If ‘-’ stands for ‘division’, ‘+’ for ‘multiplication’, ‘÷’ for ‘subtraction’ and ‘×’ for ‘addition’, which one of the following equations is correct? </br> यदि ‘-’ का अर्थ ‘भाग’, ‘+’ का अर्थ ‘गुणा’, ‘÷’ का अर्थ ‘घटा’ और ‘×’ का अर्थ ‘जमा’, तो निम्नलिखित में से कौन सा सही है? @6 + 20 - 12 ÷ 7 - 1 = 38@6 - 20 ÷ 12 × 7 + 1 = 57@6 + 20 - 12 ÷ 7 × 1 = 62@6 ÷ 20 × 12 + 7 - 1 = 70@4@6 - 20 + 12 × 7 ÷ 1 = 70